Atletico Madrid has named a powerful squad to face Liverpool in tonight’s UEFA Champions League round of 16 second-leg tie at Anfield. Atletico Madrid manager Diego Simeone, has named a 24-man squad to tackle Jurgen Klopp’s side in a post on the club’s official website on Tuesday. Simeone’s men defeated the Premier League leaders 1-0 in the first leg in Spain last month. The La Liga giants head to the game after playing a 2-2 draw against Sevilla last weekend. Below is Atletico Madrid squad against Liverpool:
Adan, Oblak, Alex, Gimenez, Arias, Lodi, Savic, Felipe, Hermoso, Trippier, Vrsaljko, Thomas, Koke, Saul, Lemar, Marcos Illorente, Hector Herrera, Vitolo, Carrasco, Joao Felix, Morata, Correa, Ivan Saponjic, Diego Costa. The kick-off time for the match is 9 pm.